Description: # ðŸ“ shapes_geometry
        
        `shapes_geometry` is a lightweight Python package for performing geometry calculations for common 2D and 3D shapes. It provides simple functions to compute area, perimeter, volume, surface area, and other geometric properties â€” perfect for students, educators, and developers building math-related tools.
        
        ---
        
        ## âœ¨ Features
        
        - ðŸ“ **2D Shapes:** Circle, Triangle, Square, Rectangle, Parallelogram, Rhombus, Trapezium, Kite, Semicircle, Regular Polygons (Pentagon, Hexagon, Octagon, Decagon)
        - ðŸ“¦ **3D Shapes:** Sphere, Cube, Cuboid, Cone, Cylinder
        - ðŸ§  Simple API with functional structure (no classes)
        - ðŸ› ï¸ Easy to extend and integrate into other Python projects
        
